unit.name: Goblin Crew
unit.desc: "What they lack in intelligence, they make up for in numbers." - Decim, the Firebringer

unit.name: Cliffpass Defender
unit.desc: "The narrow trail is the least of your worries!" - Selyne the Bold Heart

unit.name: Celerity
unit.desc: "It means to be very fast, look it up!" - Defensive Researcher

unit.name: Wortwog
unit.desc: "Why are ya' cryin'? It'll grow back."

unit.desc: "In the shade or in the glade, there is always a blade." - Treeblade Saying

unit.name: Shadowcrafter
unit.desc: "Never trust a magpie." - Kor'ladesh, Minos Poisonmancer

unit.name: Phoenix
unit.desc: Born once in a thousand years, the Phoenix can never truly die.

unit.name: Firetail Dragon
unit.desc: "Often found roaming the great plains of Nuramatha, it is hypothesized that they are the reason for the lack of forests in the area." - Researcher's Notes

unit.name: Bone Wielder
unit.desc: "The boomerangs work great, the problem is that the goblins can never stay still long enough for it to return." - Discarded Researcher Notes

unit.name: Enigma
unit.desc: Enigma have been known to challenge adventurers with complex puzzles with the prize being their very life.

unit.name: Rugarth, Fallen Bones

unit.name: Released Captives
unit.desc: "We thought death would be the end."

unit.name: Doxum's Construct
unit.desc: "Who's the 'little one' now Jubjub?! HAHAHAHAhahahaha!" - Doxum

unit.name: Gob Launcher
unit.desc: "One... two... FIVE!"

unit.name: Sheltering Wing
unit.desc: "Gaining the trust of a dragon is better than forging any weapon."

unit.name: Tiamat
unit.desc: "Born of Chaos and Aether, Tiamat was overwhelmed by its Chaotic nature and eventually turned on those it was to protect." - Ballad of Vularias IX

unit.name: Ribbitaksu
unit.desc: "Mushi no ken wo kurae!"

unit.desc: "You don't want to bug the frogs in the wastes. Trust me. They take their rocks very seriously." - Ol' Cedric

unit.name: Spelltalon
unit.desc: It melds with shadow, it is the night.

unit.name: Otherworldly Archer
unit.desc: The spirits of the past guide the hands of the present.

unit.name: Charon
unit.desc: "I swear to HADES I will turn this boat around! Is that what you want?!"

unit.name: Relentless Dead
unit.desc: "Death only made them more dangerous." - Frigore Survivor

unit.name: Battleborn Destrier
unit.desc: The vampires of Interitus use foul magic to form horses born only for warfare.

unit.name: Cress, Flamespeaker
unit.desc: Legends told of an ancient frog that could speak the tongue of dragons.

unit.name: Crossbomb Gremlin
unit.desc: Destructive as they are crazy.

unit.name: Crossbomb Rebel
unit.desc: The goblin's joyous laughter echoed even above the explosions.

unit.name: Sandspirit Whisperer
unit.desc: The sands of the desert bend to their command, drowning their enemies in body and mind.

unit.name: Orbos
unit.desc: "Fire is bad." - Novice Adventurer's Advice Volume II

unit.name: Targeting Orbos
unit.desc: "Fire is best to be avoided." - Novice Adventurer's Advice Volume IV

unit.name: Firebeam Orbos
unit.desc: "Not again!"

unit.name: Coven Knight

unit.name: Corpsedancer
unit.desc: "They turn the fallen into their own, corpses risen to fight for the enemy!" - No'tuka, Front Line Soldier

unit.name: Kiki
unit.desc: "The Kiki were armed by mountain tribes to ward off enemies, they didn't expect the Kiki to turn on them too." - History of Arcantica III

unit.name: Deatheye Owl
unit.desc: "Came 'cross one in'na dead o' night. Eye glow'in fire, felt like it reached 'ight in an' touched ma' soul." - Mort, Village Guard

unit.name: Searsteel Soldier
unit.desc: At Goblin Rise Stronghold they have created devices to keep elementals and channel their strength. The elementals don't seem to mind the company.

unit.name: Raptrys
unit.desc: A shadow upon the night sky.

unit.name: Mag "The Pebble" Ma
unit.desc: "It's you that he's cooking."
